<td><FONT SIZE="1" FACE="Verdana, Arial" COLOR="#00ff00">Originally posted by Icon on 07-29-2001 09:52 PM<BR></FONT>
<TEXTAREA NAME="EditedMessage" ROWS=10 COLS=45 WRAP="VIRTUAL">I'd normally agree with you except for one thing:

Ashran specifically said we could expect an update within 2 to 4 weeks, almost two months ago.  When ones says they will release something, posts it on the site, and especially gives a timeframe, they have an obligation to fulfill.  True, Ash doesn't owe us anything, but he created his own obligation when he posted that update.

Actually, I wouldn't have a problem if it was released a few days late, maybe a week late.  But we are beyond tardiness.  I realize that Ash didn't want to give a date, and only did to cut down on everyone whining at him, but he *did* give a date.  I would expect that he'd post the date a bit off to give himself some extra time to comply.  A cushion if you will.  Yet maybe he did do that, but so far I have seen no evidence that the Emu is even close to a release.  All I want to see is a peice of shit release just to let us all know *something* is being done.

Ash's abilities far outweigh mine, so I can't really talk much, but this long for a beta, maybe even alpha, release seems a bit out of hand.  

To Ashran: -- To be honest, if the other projects you keep talking about are planned on being released via the HQ site, then we wont mind if you put them on hold for awhile.  Especially since you never announced them or gave them a date.  If they are for something else, then maybe you should cut back a little and concentrate more on the Emu.  Or at least tell us what is going on.

What gets me the most is that you keep giving general statements like "other projects" and "we're working on it" and stuff, but nothing specific.  The vague promises you contently make hurt more then they help.  IMHO, you should give specific information regarding how much progress is being made every so often, lik daily or weekly or something, and maybe even leak some info about these 'other projects'... like what they are, what they do, or maybe just what they are for and how far you are on them.  Could be included with the daily, weekly, or whatever, update I'm asking for.

And if you are too busy for the update, I'm sure lots of people would be willing to do it for you. Hell, if Xith, Draigon, or someone else in the HQ crew doesn't want to do it, then let ME.  I'd be happy to sit around and take some vague hints and turn them into a progress page.

Shit you already HAVE a progress page, but that was for the old emu.

Seriously man, throw us a bone here.

 - Icon
-----------------
In memory of MasTerKeyZ.

